               <physDesc>
                  <p>The interpretation of sādittu as “oiling” is based on the recorded meaning of
                     “to rub on carefully, as oil […]” recorded by Winslow 1862, s.v. சாதி, and
                     repeated by the Tamil Lexicon, too. Whether this is the actual meaning in this
                     passage remains unclear, since this is the only occurrence we have encountered
                     so far, but it definitely makes sense in this context.</p>
               </physDesc>
